Subject: [ghostium] NavigatorUAData (UA-CH) hook

Spec-E wiring. Anchors at top of ``navigator_ua_data.cc``. The real
calls into ``FingerprintNoiseSource``'s UA-metadata predicates land
inside the four NavigatorUAData accessors:

  * ``brands`` (low-entropy hint)
  * ``mobile`` (low-entropy hint)
  * ``platform`` (low-entropy hint)
  * ``getHighEntropyValues`` (architecture / bitness / model /
    platformVersion / fullVersion / fullVersionList / wow64)

The WebContents-level UA override applied by Spec-C's
``EmulationBridge`` already populates these via ``UserAgentMetadata``;
this hook is a defensive fallback for the same reason as 0008.

---
 third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_ua_data.cc | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_ua_data.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_ua_data.cc
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_ua_data.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_ua_data.cc
@@ -1,3 +1,10 @@
